para_trans: Regarding administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report (DPR) submitted by the local bodies for the works to be taken up out of the prize money received under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0.
Umarkhed Municipal Council, District Yavatmal.
Government of Maharashtra
Department of Environment and Climate Change
Government Decision No: MAWA 0825 / P.No. 959 (37) / T.H.2
Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032
Date: October 15, 2025

Read: (1) Government Decision, Environment and Climate Change Department No. Mission - 2024 / P.No.66 /. Government Decision dated 1st September, 2024 (2), Department of Environment and Climate Change No. Abhiyaan-20219 / P.S. No.57 / T. Preamble: My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4. The procedure for the award of cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories of the award has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 26th August, 2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.

Government Decision: Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, the total amount received by the Umarkhed Municipal Council under My Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 is Rs. 50.00 The focus will be on the works to be undertaken out of the prize money of Rs. The Detailed Project Report costing ₹50,00, 000.00 (Rupees fifty lakhs only) has been submitted by the Principal, Umarkhed Municipal Council with the technical approval of the City Engineer, Amravati Municipal Corporation.

The proposal was submitted by the Umarkhed Municipal Council. The Committee constituted under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change held its meetings on 26th August, 2025.
Government Decision No: MAWA-0825 / P.No.159 (37) / T. A. 1.

was considered. As per the recommendation made by the said committee, the total amount submitted by the Umarkhed Municipal Council is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing ₹50,00, 000.00 (Rupees fifty lakhs only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions 1) The Umarkhed Municipal Council shall be the operational mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The execution of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed in the next & month from the date of approval by the Administrator.
4) Expenditure in excess of the prize money should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, Umarkhed Municipal Council has been allotted Rs. A prize of ₹1 lakh has been received. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them.

Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the balance of the prize money to the Umarkhed Municipal Council is Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (Rupees Twenty Five Lakhs only) through Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
